review_blob:

review_blob:

Talk about a smack in the face! I took a good 5 minutes for my taste buds to figure out what I had just done to them. Thin, and best cold. Congrats to Rogue for doing exactly what the bottle says. I can taste the chocolate, the raspberry and the soft pretzel comes through with the yeast and salty notes. Bravo!!

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Smooth with a punch.  Sweet/bitter balanced.  Smells of malt and sugars.  Beige head with pour out of bottle, almost a dark cherry color in the glass.
My go-to beer.  Strong and nutty.  Has a beautiful carmel color and a bitter finish that lingers.
